title: ICE `VtableImpl ... did not contain projection for `Obligation

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

body:
My code is probably wrong in some way because I'm a real n00b to Rust but since the compiler output tells me to submit a bug report I will obey. Possible duplicate of https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/20347 but I know too little to be sure.

## Source code

``` rust
use std::iter::AdditiveIterator;

struct Fibonacci {
    curr: uint,
    next: uint,
}

fn fib() -> Fibonacci {
    Fibonacci {curr: 1, next: 2}
}

impl Iterator for Fibonacci {
    fn next(&mut self) -> uint {
        let curr = self.curr;
        self.curr = self.next;
        self.next = curr + self.next;
        curr
    }
}

fn initial() -> uint {
    fib().take(5).sum();
}

fn main() {
    println!("Initial: {}", initial());
}
```
